00:02:16.179 --> 00:02:18.306
Did you drop this baby?

00:02:18.389 --> 00:02:20.391
Jesus Christ, no.

00:02:25.563 --> 00:02:28.566
Inform the ambulance
that we have a situation.

00:02:28.650 --> 00:02:31.611
All right.
Molly.

00:02:31.694 --> 00:02:34.531
I've never seen this.

00:02:37.492 --> 00:02:41.371
It appears that your baby
has sustained some fractures...

00:02:41.454 --> 00:02:43.456
while inside your uterus.

00:02:47.001 --> 00:02:49.003
His arms and his legs are broken.

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:41.306
This is Eastrail 177.

00:03:41.389 --> 00:03:43.516
Next stop, Philadelphia.

00:04:17.467 --> 00:04:19.469
Are you alone?

00:04:21.137 --> 00:04:23.223
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:05:09.269 --> 00:05:11.479
Someone left this magazine.

00:05:11.563 --> 00:05:13.565
Want to take a look at it?

00:05:13.648 --> 00:05:15.650
Could I take a look at that one?

00:05:22.031 --> 00:05:23.908
Thanks.

00:05:23.992 --> 00:05:26.911
- You like sports?
- It's my field.

00:05:26.995 --> 00:05:28.997
I represent athletes.
I'm an agent.

00:05:30.999 --> 00:05:34.294
Are you looking for any
male synchronized swimmers?

00:05:34.377 --> 00:05:37.172
- I'm thinking about getting into that.
- Is that right?

00:05:40.592 --> 00:05:42.594
I'm afraid of water.

00:05:42.677 --> 00:05:44.679
Think that's a problem?

00:05:52.187 --> 00:05:55.106
You represent someone
in Philadelphia?

00:05:55.190 --> 00:05:57.442
I'm meeting this player
from Temple University.

00:05:57.525 --> 00:05:59.527
He's a cornerback.

00:05:59.611 --> 00:06:03.364
This kid is 6'1 ", 210 pounds.

00:06:03.448 --> 00:06:07.619
He runs a 40 in 4.3 seconds.
He's gonna be a god.

00:06:07.702 --> 00:06:10.705
Do you like football?

00:06:10.788 --> 00:06:12.790
Not really.

00:06:24.052 --> 00:06:27.764
- I'm David Dunn.
- Kelly.

00:06:27.847 --> 00:06:30.600
- Hi.
- Hi, nice to meet you.

00:06:30.683 --> 00:06:32.685
Nice-Nice to meet you.

00:06:40.276 --> 00:06:42.862
How long are you gonna be
in Philadelphia?

00:06:50.995 --> 00:06:54.123
- I'm married.
- Great.

00:06:54.207 --> 00:06:57.043
- I'm sorry.
- What are you talking about?

00:06:59.838 --> 00:07:02.090
I-

00:07:02.173 --> 00:07:06.469
I think you misunderstood
what I was, uh...

00:07:06.553 --> 00:07:08.721
- s-saying-
- I know.

00:07:11.307 --> 00:07:13.643
I think I'm gonna find another seat.

00:07:13.726 --> 00:07:16.187
I- I didn't mean, uh-

00:08:55.828 --> 00:08:59.123
That's what he failed to realize.
I look classy, not trashy.

00:08:59.207 --> 00:09:04.045
I look classy too. What about me?
Don't I look classy?

00:09:04.128 --> 00:09:06.548
But I'm afraid you forgot this!

00:09:06.631 --> 00:09:10.802
- And this! And-
- Where has you been, Banana?

00:09:10.885 --> 00:09:13.137
Now I've got you, weasel.

00:09:13.221 --> 00:09:17.934
Some cars are still on fire,
and the debris is everywhere.

00:09:18.017 --> 00:09:19.936
We are not sure at this time, uh...

00:09:20.019 --> 00:09:22.522
how rescue personnel will be able
to get on scene at all.

00:09:22.605 --> 00:09:25.191
If you'rejust tuning in,
Eastrail train number 177...

00:09:25.275 --> 00:09:27.694
has derailed
just outside Philadelphia.

00:09:27.777 --> 00:09:30.113
And we're bringing you
live coverage from Skycam 4.

00:09:30.196 --> 00:09:32.532
Yes, that is- It appears
to be a rescue ambulance...

00:09:32.615 --> 00:09:35.535
and there are more behind it
I can see on the access road.

00:09:35.618 --> 00:09:38.121
I don't know how close they're
gonna be able to get, David.

00:09:38.204 --> 00:09:40.999
These are woods and, uh, trees.

00:09:41.082 --> 00:09:43.501
It's gonna be a very
difficult rescue effort.

00:09:59.601 --> 00:10:01.603
Try to hack some of that off.

00:10:14.490 --> 00:10:18.203
Hi. I'm Dr Dubin.

00:10:18.286 --> 00:10:21.998
You're in the emergency room in
the Philadelphia City Hospital.

00:10:22.081 --> 00:10:24.083
You were in a serious accident.

00:10:25.210 --> 00:10:27.504
Look at me.

00:10:27.587 --> 00:10:29.589
How are you feeling?

00:10:31.466 --> 00:10:33.676
- Okay.
- Good.

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:36.221
I'm gonna ask you some questions.

00:10:36.304 --> 00:10:40.099
Have you ever had any heart
or asthma problems in the past?

00:10:40.183 --> 00:10:44.354
- No.
- Kidney or renal problems?

00:10:44.437 --> 00:10:46.940
- No.
- Any allergies?

00:10:49.317 --> 00:10:51.319
No.

00:10:56.115 --> 00:10:58.117
Where were you sitting
on the train?

00:11:02.121 --> 00:11:04.958
- Against the window.
- In the passenger car?

00:11:07.210 --> 00:11:09.212
Yeah.

00:11:11.422 --> 00:11:15.176
- Where are the other passengers?
- Was your family travelling with you?

00:11:17.846 --> 00:11:19.764
No.

00:11:19.848 --> 00:11:22.559
Did you get up from your seat?

00:11:28.189 --> 00:11:31.234
Are you certain
you were in the passenger car?

00:11:36.489 --> 00:11:38.491
Yes.

00:11:46.040 --> 00:11:48.877
Why are you looking at me like that?

00:11:48.960 --> 00:11:51.004
Your train derailed.

00:11:51.087 --> 00:11:53.840
Some kind of malfunction.

00:11:53.923 --> 00:11:56.885
They only found
two people alive so far-

00:11:56.968 --> 00:11:58.970
you and this man.

00:12:01.347 --> 00:12:04.684
His skull was cracked open and
most of his left side was crushed.

00:12:06.853 --> 00:12:08.980
And to answer your question,
there are two reasons...

00:12:09.063 --> 00:12:12.108
why I'm looking at you like this.

00:12:12.192 --> 00:12:14.986
One, because it seems
in a few minutes...

00:12:15.069 --> 00:12:19.365
that you will officially be
the only survivor of this train wreck.

00:12:19.449 --> 00:12:22.368
And two...

00:12:22.452 --> 00:12:24.454
because you didn't break one bone.

00:12:25.872 --> 00:12:27.874
You don't have a scratch on you.

00:14:13.938 --> 00:14:15.899
David?

00:14:18.568 --> 00:14:22.488
What happened in New York?

00:14:24.324 --> 00:14:26.701
I don't think I got the job.

00:14:28.536 --> 00:14:31.706
I'm still going to, uh-

00:14:31.789 --> 00:14:34.542
I'm still moving there.

00:14:34.626 --> 00:14:36.628
Just-

00:14:37.754 --> 00:14:39.756
Uh, just-just not now.

00:14:44.761 --> 00:14:46.930
Good night.

00:14:50.058 --> 00:14:52.060
Good night.

00:15:04.030 --> 00:15:06.074
Sara Elaston...

00:15:06.157 --> 00:15:09.327
social worker at
Broad and Locust Community Centre.

00:15:10.578 --> 00:15:12.747
We pray for your soul.

00:15:14.916 --> 00:15:18.044
Kevin Elliot, businessman...

00:15:18.127 --> 00:15:21.005
father of six.

00:15:21.089 --> 00:15:23.091
We pray for your soul.

00:15:24.676 --> 00:15:26.845
Glen Stevens...

00:15:26.928 --> 00:15:30.223
researcher in the area
of leukemia...

00:15:30.306 --> 00:15:32.308
at Drexel University.

00:15:34.102 --> 00:15:36.104
We pray for your soul.

00:15:37.897 --> 00:15:40.066
Jennifer Pennyman...

00:15:40.149 --> 00:15:44.320
third-grade teacher
at Jefferson Elementary.

00:15:46.531 --> 00:15:48.533
We pray for your soul.

00:16:55.600 --> 00:16:58.770
- Yes?
- Is Noel in, ma'am?

00:16:58.853 --> 00:17:00.855
No, sir, he is not.

00:17:02.273 --> 00:17:05.109
I read about you in the paper.

00:17:05.193 --> 00:17:08.446
- What?
- I was in an accident once too.

00:17:08.530 --> 00:17:11.533
A horse almost trampled me to death.

00:17:11.616 --> 00:17:13.618
- Wow.
- Had him put down.

00:17:16.287 --> 00:17:18.289
That's a sad story.

00:17:21.167 --> 00:17:26.089
Could- Could you ask Noel
something for me, please?

00:17:26.172 --> 00:17:28.341
Proceed.

00:17:28.424 --> 00:17:30.468
Would you ask him to check
how many sick days I've taken...

00:17:30.552 --> 00:17:32.679
since I've worked here?

00:17:32.762 --> 00:17:35.640
- That the entire message?
- Yes, ma'am.

00:17:39.561 --> 00:17:41.563
Thank you.

00:18:19.809 --> 00:18:21.603
Hey, Noel.

00:18:21.686 --> 00:18:23.938
What, you hit your head on that train?

00:18:24.022 --> 00:18:26.024
Get your brain
to start working again?

00:18:27.567 --> 00:18:30.278
- What?
- Forty dollars.

00:18:31.905 --> 00:18:34.616
- Forty dollars what?
- You're gettin' a $40-a-week raise.

00:18:34.699 --> 00:18:36.701
That's it.

00:18:37.827 --> 00:18:41.039
I checked. You were right.
You've never taken a sick day.

00:18:41.122 --> 00:18:44.834
Five years, no sick day.
I get it. You want a raise.

00:18:44.918 --> 00:18:46.878
Smart way to make your point.

00:19:13.613 --> 00:19:16.199
- Is Joseph okay?
- Yeah.

00:19:16.282 --> 00:19:18.827
- He's asleep.
- Oh.

00:19:22.831 --> 00:19:25.959
I wanted to ask you a question.

00:19:26.042 --> 00:19:28.253
It's gonna sound a little strange,
but, uh...

00:19:28.336 --> 00:19:31.297
just think about it
for a second, okay?

00:19:31.381 --> 00:19:34.092
Okay.

00:19:34.175 --> 00:19:36.344
When's the last time I was sick?

00:19:36.427 --> 00:19:38.429
Do you remember?

00:19:41.975 --> 00:19:43.977
Um, I-I don't know.

00:19:46.020 --> 00:19:48.857
It's been a while.

00:19:48.940 --> 00:19:52.735
I haven't been sick this year,
I know that.

00:19:52.819 --> 00:19:54.946
Okay.

00:19:55.029 --> 00:19:57.031
Do you remember me gettin' sick?

00:20:00.201 --> 00:20:02.495
Um...

00:20:02.579 --> 00:20:04.873
not a specific day.

00:20:04.956 --> 00:20:07.167
And what's-what's this about?

00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:13.006
Audrey, do you remember me
ever getting sick?

00:20:13.089 --> 00:20:15.967
In the three years
we lived in this house?

00:20:16.050 --> 00:20:18.136
In the old apartment?

00:20:18.219 --> 00:20:21.181
Before Joseph was born?
Before we ever got married?

00:20:25.518 --> 00:20:27.520
I- I can't remember.

00:20:29.397 --> 00:20:31.733
Don't you think
that's kind of weird...

00:20:31.816 --> 00:20:35.987
not remembering one cold
or a-a fever or a sore throat?

00:20:38.281 --> 00:20:40.283
What do you think it means?

00:20:45.038 --> 00:20:47.957
Um...

00:20:48.041 --> 00:20:51.920
I think it means
I'm probably too tired to remember.

00:21:33.336 --> 00:21:37.715
No more sittin' in this room.
I let it go on long enough.

00:21:37.799 --> 00:21:40.969
I'm not goin' out there any more.
I'm not getting hurt again.

00:21:41.052 --> 00:21:45.390
- This was the last time, I told you.
- You can't do anything about that.

00:21:45.473 --> 00:21:47.809
You might fall between
this chair and that television.

00:21:47.892 --> 00:21:50.895
If that's what God has planned for you,
that's what's gonna happen.

00:21:50.979 --> 00:21:53.398
You can't hide from it
sittin' in a room.

00:21:57.443 --> 00:22:01.281
They call me Mr Glass at school
because I break like glass.

00:22:06.411 --> 00:22:08.413
You make this decision now...

00:22:09.831 --> 00:22:11.833
to be afraid...

00:22:13.459 --> 00:22:15.628
and you will never turn back.

00:22:17.338 --> 00:22:22.177
Your whole life,
you will always be afraid.

00:22:36.983 --> 00:22:39.527
- I got a present for you.
- Why?

00:22:41.237 --> 00:22:43.239
Forget why.

00:22:45.825 --> 00:22:47.827
You want it or not?

00:22:50.788 --> 00:22:52.999
Well, go get it, then.

00:22:53.082 --> 00:22:56.044
Where is it?

00:22:56.127 --> 00:22:58.755
On a bench...

00:22:58.838 --> 00:23:00.840
across the street.

00:23:14.896 --> 00:23:16.898
Someone's gonna take it.

00:23:18.900 --> 00:23:21.653
Then you better get out there soon.

00:24:36.102 --> 00:24:38.104
I bought a whole bunch.

00:24:42.609 --> 00:24:44.694
There'll be one of these
waitin' for you...

00:24:44.777 --> 00:24:46.946
every time you want
to come out here.

00:24:53.661 --> 00:24:56.789
They say this one
has a surprise ending.

00:25:05.673 --> 00:25:08.718
This is from Fritz Campion's
own library.

00:25:08.801 --> 00:25:13.723
This is before the first issue of
the comic book hit the stands in 1968.

00:25:13.806 --> 00:25:17.852
It's a classic depiction
of good versus evil.

00:25:17.936 --> 00:25:21.940
Notice the square jaw of Slayer,
common in most comic heroes.

00:25:22.023 --> 00:25:25.777
And the slightly disproportionate size
of Jaguaro's head to his body.

00:25:25.860 --> 00:25:29.948
This again is common,
but only in villains.

00:25:30.031 --> 00:25:32.450
The thing to notice about this piece...

00:25:32.534 --> 00:25:36.538
the thing that makes it
very, very special...

00:25:36.621 --> 00:25:39.707
is its realistic depiction
of its figures.

00:25:39.791 --> 00:25:41.835
When the characters
reached the magazine...

00:25:41.918 --> 00:25:44.003
they were exaggerated...

00:25:44.087 --> 00:25:46.339
as always happens.

00:25:46.422 --> 00:25:50.176
This is vintage.

00:25:53.054 --> 00:25:55.056
Well...

00:26:00.144 --> 00:26:02.647
wrap it up.

00:26:02.730 --> 00:26:05.149
You've made a considerably
wise decision.

00:26:10.572 --> 00:26:12.574
Well, my kid's gonna go berserk.

00:26:16.119 --> 00:26:18.163
Once again, please?

00:26:18.246 --> 00:26:21.040
My son Jeb-
it's a gift for him.

00:26:21.124 --> 00:26:24.002
- How old is Jeb?
- He's four.

00:26:27.005 --> 00:26:29.090
No.

00:26:29.174 --> 00:26:32.927
No, no, no, no, no.

00:26:34.429 --> 00:26:36.806
You need to go. Now.

00:26:38.600 --> 00:26:40.727
What'd-What'd I say?

00:26:40.810 --> 00:26:44.147
Do you see any Teletubbies in here?

00:26:44.230 --> 00:26:46.274
Do you see a slender plastic tag
clipped to my shirt...

00:26:46.357 --> 00:26:48.526
with my name printed on it?

00:26:48.610 --> 00:26:51.529
Did you see a little Asian child with
a blank expression sitting outside...

00:26:51.613 --> 00:26:55.366
in a mechanical helicopter that shakes
when you put quarters in it?

00:26:55.450 --> 00:26:59.078
No? Well, that's what
you see at a toy store...

00:26:59.162 --> 00:27:01.164
and you must think
you're in a toy store because...

00:27:01.247 --> 00:27:04.792
you're here shopping
for an infant named Jeb.

00:27:04.876 --> 00:27:07.879
Now, one of us
has made a gross error...

00:27:07.962 --> 00:27:11.174
and wasted the other person's
valuable time.

00:27:11.257 --> 00:27:13.384
This is an art gallery,
my friend...

00:27:13.468 --> 00:27:17.222
and this is a piece of art.

00:27:32.570 --> 00:27:34.572
We're by appointment only.

00:27:36.324 --> 00:27:38.952
- I got a card from this store.
- Congratulations.

00:27:39.035 --> 00:27:42.664
You have a mailbox.
The exhibition isn't for two weeks.

00:27:42.747 --> 00:27:45.583
This one was under
the windshield wiper of my car.

00:27:48.461 --> 00:27:51.548
How certain are you that
you've never taken ill?

00:27:51.631 --> 00:27:54.175
Seventy-five percent.

00:27:54.259 --> 00:27:57.720
Well, that's not
certain at all, is it?

00:27:59.138 --> 00:28:02.058
That's hole number one.

00:28:02.141 --> 00:28:05.353
I'm going to be extremely skeptical
about all this.

00:28:05.436 --> 00:28:07.438
About all what?

00:28:08.940 --> 00:28:12.151
I'm assuming you've never been injured.
Would I be wrong in that assumption?

00:28:12.235 --> 00:28:14.237
Dad's been injured.

00:28:15.530 --> 00:28:18.533
Is the child correct?

00:28:18.616 --> 00:28:22.745
Yes, sir. In college,
I was in a car accident.

00:28:22.829 --> 00:28:27.709
- Was it serious?
- He couldn't play football any more.

00:28:27.792 --> 00:28:29.794
That's hole number two.

00:28:31.588 --> 00:28:33.590
That's a big one.

00:28:37.177 --> 00:28:41.139
Mr Price, can we talk about
the note that you left on my car?

00:28:41.222 --> 00:28:44.475
I've studied the form
of comics intimately.

00:28:44.559 --> 00:28:46.603
I've spent a third of my life
in a hospital bed...

00:28:46.686 --> 00:28:49.856
with nothing else to do but read.

00:28:49.939 --> 00:28:51.941
I believe comics
are our last link...

00:28:52.025 --> 00:28:55.737
to an ancient way
of passing on history.

00:28:55.820 --> 00:28:57.989
The Egyptians drew on walls.

00:28:58.072 --> 00:29:02.327
Countries all over the world still pass
on knowledge through pictorial forms.

00:29:02.410 --> 00:29:04.579
I believe comics
are a form of history...

00:29:04.662 --> 00:29:08.249
that someone somewhere
felt or experienced.

00:29:08.333 --> 00:29:10.668
Then, of course,
those experiences and that history...

00:29:10.752 --> 00:29:13.796
got chewed up in the commercial
machine, got jazzed up...

00:29:13.880 --> 00:29:16.758
made titillating,
cartooned for the sale rack.

00:29:18.134 --> 00:29:21.554
This city has seen its share
of disasters.

00:29:21.638 --> 00:29:24.140
I watched the aftermath
of that plane crash.

00:29:24.224 --> 00:29:26.768
I watched the carnage
of the hotel fire.

00:29:26.851 --> 00:29:31.773
I watched the news waiting to hear
a very specific combination of words...

00:29:31.856 --> 00:29:34.359
but they never came.

00:29:34.442 --> 00:29:38.196
Then one day I saw a news story
about a train accident...

00:29:38.279 --> 00:29:40.323
and I heard them.

00:29:40.406 --> 00:29:42.492
"There is a sole survivor...

00:29:42.575 --> 00:29:45.703
and he is miraculously unharmed. "

00:29:48.706 --> 00:29:52.168
I have something called
osteogenesis imperfecta.

00:29:52.252 --> 00:29:54.254
It's a genetic disorder.

00:29:54.337 --> 00:29:56.339
I don't make a particular
protein very well...

00:29:56.422 --> 00:29:58.967
and it makes my bones
very low in density.

00:29:59.050 --> 00:30:01.344
Very easy to break.

00:30:01.427 --> 00:30:03.972
I've had 54 breaks in my life...

00:30:04.055 --> 00:30:08.852
and I have the tamest version
of this disorder, type one.

00:30:08.935 --> 00:30:12.647
There are type two,
type three, type four.

00:30:12.730 --> 00:30:14.732
Type fours don't last very long.

00:30:16.359 --> 00:30:19.362
So that's how it popped into my head.

00:30:19.445 --> 00:30:22.282
If there is someone
like me in the world...

00:30:22.365 --> 00:30:24.617
and I'm at one end
of the spectrum...

00:30:24.701 --> 00:30:26.744
couldn't there be someone else...

00:30:26.828 --> 00:30:29.080
the opposite of me
at the other end?

00:30:29.164 --> 00:30:33.543
Someone who doesn't get sick, who
doesn't get hurt like the rest of us?

00:30:33.626 --> 00:30:37.422
And he probably
doesn't even know it.

00:30:37.505 --> 00:30:42.719
The kind of person
these stories are about.

00:30:42.802 --> 00:30:47.932
A person put here
to protect the rest of us.

00:30:48.016 --> 00:30:50.101
To guard us.

00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:57.108
- You think my dad's a real-
- I don't think anything right now.

00:30:57.192 --> 00:30:59.652
It's a possibility-

00:30:59.736 --> 00:31:01.738
one with many holes.

00:31:05.283 --> 00:31:07.952
Joseph, don't take
another sip of that water.

00:31:11.122 --> 00:31:13.208
- Go throw it in the trash.
- But Dad-

00:31:13.291 --> 00:31:15.293
Do it now, please.

00:31:24.928 --> 00:31:28.556
I see guys like you
all the time in my work.

00:31:28.640 --> 00:31:32.143
You find someone you want
to take advantage of...

00:31:32.227 --> 00:31:35.688
you tell them a fantastic story...

00:31:35.772 --> 00:31:38.650
and somewhere in there you say it:

00:31:38.733 --> 00:31:41.694
"I just need
your credit card number...

00:31:41.778 --> 00:31:43.780
a small down payment. "

00:31:46.449 --> 00:31:48.451
This morning was the first morning
that I could remember...

00:31:48.535 --> 00:31:50.537
that I didn't open my eyes
and feel...

00:31:53.373 --> 00:31:55.500
sadness.

00:31:59.087 --> 00:32:02.257
I thought the person that wrote
that note had an answer for me.

00:32:09.180 --> 00:32:12.225
I'm gonna leave now.

00:32:12.308 --> 00:32:14.310
Good luck with your exhibition.

00:32:14.394 --> 00:32:16.896
So, what kind of job
do you have, David?

00:32:16.980 --> 00:32:19.023
You said you've met guys like me
in your work.

00:32:19.107 --> 00:32:23.695
- What exactly is it that you do?
- I work at the University Stadium.

00:32:23.778 --> 00:32:26.364
I'm a security guard.

00:34:42.041 --> 00:34:44.252
Hi.

00:34:44.335 --> 00:34:47.172
I've come to a decision.

00:34:47.255 --> 00:34:49.632
Okay.

00:34:49.716 --> 00:34:52.260
I just wanna ask you something, okay?

00:34:52.343 --> 00:34:55.889
And you can be totally honest.

00:34:55.972 --> 00:34:59.601
I'm prepared for any answer,
and-and it won't affect me.

00:35:02.187 --> 00:35:04.981
Have you been with anyone?

00:35:05.064 --> 00:35:07.317
I mean, since we've
been having problems.

00:35:07.400 --> 00:35:09.402
The answer won't affect me.

00:35:12.614 --> 00:35:15.283
I just need to know, you know?

00:35:15.366 --> 00:35:17.368
I mean, it won't affect me
either way.

00:35:19.787 --> 00:35:21.789
No.

00:35:29.672 --> 00:35:31.925
Sorry, David.
I'm sorry.

00:35:37.222 --> 00:35:39.390
Anyway...

00:35:39.474 --> 00:35:41.476
my decision is...

00:35:44.729 --> 00:35:46.731
that I want to start again.

00:35:50.360 --> 00:35:53.112
And I want it to be
like it was in the beginning.

00:35:56.491 --> 00:35:59.828
And it's a big deal that
you walked away from that train.

00:36:02.789 --> 00:36:04.833
I feel like it's a second chance.

00:36:11.047 --> 00:36:14.300
And if you feel like
asking me out sometime...

00:36:14.384 --> 00:36:16.386
that'd be okay.

00:36:18.847 --> 00:36:20.849
Okay.

00:36:33.528 --> 00:36:36.072
- Dunn.
- Go for Dunn.

00:36:36.156 --> 00:36:40.451
Yeah, it's Jenkins. Look, we got a guy
over at gate 17-C with a bogus ticket.

00:36:40.535 --> 00:36:44.581
Says he knows you.
He won't tell me his name.

00:36:44.664 --> 00:36:47.375
What's he look like?

00:36:47.458 --> 00:36:49.669
Why is it, do you think, that
of all the professions in the world...

00:36:49.752 --> 00:36:51.754
you chose protection?

00:36:53.840 --> 00:36:56.634
- You are a very strange man.
- You could have been a tax accountant.

00:36:56.718 --> 00:36:59.596
You could have owned your own gym. You
could've opened a chain of restaurants.

00:36:59.679 --> 00:37:02.098
You could've done
one of 10,000 things.

00:37:02.182 --> 00:37:06.311
But in the end,
you chose to protect people.

00:37:06.394 --> 00:37:08.897
You made that decision,
and I find that...

00:37:08.980 --> 00:37:10.982
very, very interesting.

00:37:12.275 --> 00:37:15.195
Now all I need is
your credit card number.

00:37:16.321 --> 00:37:18.323
That last part was a joke.

00:37:22.494 --> 00:37:26.998
- You're a big sports fan, are you?
- It's starting to intrigue me.

00:37:28.291 --> 00:37:30.710
It gets heaviest
ten minutes before kickoff.

00:37:43.097 --> 00:37:45.391
Programme here.
Programme.

00:37:45.475 --> 00:37:47.477
Programme.

00:37:49.270 --> 00:37:53.066
Programme. Programme here.

00:37:53.149 --> 00:37:55.151
- Rich, why don't we pat down?
- Right.

00:37:55.235 --> 00:37:57.237
- Just give me a minute.
- Is there a problem?

00:37:57.320 --> 00:37:59.322
I'm sorry.
I'm gonna have to search you.

00:37:59.405 --> 00:38:02.784
- It's nothing personal.
- The tall guy in the camouflage jacket.

00:38:02.867 --> 00:38:07.413
Sometimes people carry weapons in here,
and they drink too much.

00:38:07.497 --> 00:38:12.168
If the team's not doing good,
bad things can happen.

00:38:12.252 --> 00:38:15.505
We do pat-downs of the crowd
to discourage people from carrying.

00:38:16.923 --> 00:38:19.551
If he's carrying,
he'll step out of line.

00:38:32.689 --> 00:38:34.691
Yeah, step right up here.

00:38:43.825 --> 00:38:48.621
Okay. I got you a seat up
in the yellow section.

00:38:48.705 --> 00:38:53.543
It's in the nosebleeds,
but at least you won't get spit on.

00:38:53.626 --> 00:38:55.879
- All right.
- How'd you know that guy you bumped...

00:38:55.962 --> 00:38:57.964
was carrying a weapon?

00:39:00.091 --> 00:39:02.343
I don't know.

00:39:02.427 --> 00:39:06.848
Maybe it was that camouflage
army jacket he was wearing.

00:39:06.931 --> 00:39:09.684
Those guys like to carry
hunting knives and stuff for show.

00:39:09.767 --> 00:39:13.146
You thought he was carrying a knife?

00:39:13.229 --> 00:39:16.316
- I thought he was carrying something, yeah.
- But not a knife.

00:39:19.944 --> 00:39:24.908
I got a picture of a silver gun
with a black grip...

00:39:24.991 --> 00:39:27.243
tucked in his pants.

00:39:27.327 --> 00:39:29.704
You know, like on TV.

00:39:31.164 --> 00:39:34.000
You have good instincts
for things like that?

00:39:34.083 --> 00:39:37.504
- Like what?
- Knowing when people have done something wrong?

00:39:41.007 --> 00:39:44.135
- Yeah.
- Have you ever tried to develop it?

00:39:46.095 --> 00:39:50.183
- I don't know what you're asking me.
- Your skill.

00:39:50.266 --> 00:39:52.435
Look, I gotta be down on
the sidelines during the game.

00:39:52.519 --> 00:39:54.771
- You can get to your seat right down-
- Characters in comics...

00:39:54.854 --> 00:39:57.357
are often attributed special powers-

00:39:57.440 --> 00:40:01.903
invisibility, X-ray vision,
things of that sort.

00:40:01.986 --> 00:40:04.572
Okay.

00:40:04.656 --> 00:40:09.285
- I don't wanna play this game any more.
- It's an exaggeration of the truth.

00:40:09.369 --> 00:40:14.582
Maybe it's based on something
as simple as instinct.

00:40:14.666 --> 00:40:17.293
- But he might not have been carrying anything.
- But he might have been carrying...

00:40:17.377 --> 00:40:20.255
a silver gun with a black grip
tucked in his pants.

00:40:20.338 --> 00:40:23.174
- Dunn.
- I gotta go.

00:40:25.593 --> 00:40:27.846
Yeah, I know.
I'll be right down.

00:40:27.929 --> 00:40:31.140
- One last question.
- What?

00:40:31.224 --> 00:40:33.601
That car accident you were in.

00:40:33.685 --> 00:40:35.687
Was there anyone else involved?

00:40:37.897 --> 00:40:41.234
Yeah.
My wife, Audrey.

00:40:41.317 --> 00:40:43.403
She was in the car with me.

00:40:45.488 --> 00:40:48.408
Have a good life, Elijah.

00:40:48.491 --> 00:40:51.870
Next time, try to buy your tickets
at an authorized sales location.

00:40:51.953 --> 00:40:55.999
- Dunn.
- I'm on my way.

00:41:00.044 --> 00:41:02.297
...into the investigation
of train 177...

00:41:02.380 --> 00:41:05.550
being conducted at the Eastrail
holding warehouses.

00:41:05.633 --> 00:41:08.178
The city council has
stepped up plans to pass a bill...

00:41:08.261 --> 00:41:11.598
requiring higher standards
for inspection and maintenance...

00:41:11.681 --> 00:41:14.350
of all rail transportation
for Philadelphia...

00:41:14.434 --> 00:41:16.436
and its outlying districts.

00:41:24.194 --> 00:41:25.862
Hold up a second!

00:42:20.875 --> 00:42:23.503
I just want to ask you something.

00:43:33.239 --> 00:43:35.909
Dad! Hey, Dad!

00:43:42.832 --> 00:43:44.834
Dad!

00:43:55.887 --> 00:43:59.641
Joseph, do you know how mad your mother would
be if she knew you were playing football?

00:43:59.724 --> 00:44:02.560
Are you gonna tell?

00:44:02.644 --> 00:44:06.105
You wanna play last of the downs?
We got a big guy like you.

00:44:06.189 --> 00:44:10.318
You could play on opposite sides.
He's Potter's cousin.

00:44:10.401 --> 00:44:12.946
He's starting cornerback
at Temple University.

00:44:13.029 --> 00:44:15.114
He's going pro in the draft.

00:44:15.198 --> 00:44:18.660
They say he can run the 40
in 4.3 seconds.

00:44:18.743 --> 00:44:20.662
Yeah, I've heard.

00:44:20.745 --> 00:44:22.747
You can beat him, Dad.

00:44:22.831 --> 00:44:25.291
- Let's beat him.
- I'm gonna go in.

00:44:25.375 --> 00:44:28.002
Just play one set of downs.
I told them you were great.

00:44:28.086 --> 00:44:30.088
- Why'd you do that?
- Just one.

00:44:30.171 --> 00:44:32.298
I'm gonna go in.
I've got some things to do.

00:44:32.382 --> 00:44:35.176
- What things?
- I'm gonna work out.

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:36.886
- I'll help you.
- No, I-I don't need-

00:44:36.970 --> 00:44:40.765
I can't play, guys!
I'm working out with my dad!

00:44:40.849 --> 00:44:43.852
Go, go.
Here we go! Ready?

00:44:43.935 --> 00:44:47.146
Hut! You're doing good.
Right there! Catch!

00:44:47.230 --> 00:44:49.524
I've gOt tO run

00:44:49.607 --> 00:44:52.193
To keep from hiding

00:44:52.277 --> 00:44:54.612
And I'm bound

00:44:54.696 --> 00:44:57.198
To keep on riding

00:44:57.282 --> 00:45:01.911
And I've got one more silver dollar

00:45:01.995 --> 00:45:04.122
How much did you put on there?

00:45:13.006 --> 00:45:16.801
You put too much.
That's 250 pounds.

00:45:16.885 --> 00:45:20.680
How much can you lift?

00:45:20.763 --> 00:45:22.807
That's the most I ever lifted.

00:45:25.310 --> 00:45:28.104
That could've been dangerous,Joseph.

00:45:28.188 --> 00:45:30.565
Why don't you go upstairs now
and let me finish up, okay?

00:45:30.648 --> 00:45:33.443
I'll take it off.
I'll help you right.

00:45:37.906 --> 00:45:41.576
You think you could have
beaten up Bruce Lee?

00:45:41.659 --> 00:45:43.495
No.

00:45:43.578 --> 00:45:46.080
I mean, if you knew karate.

00:45:46.164 --> 00:45:48.166
No.

00:45:52.212 --> 00:45:55.340
Well, what if he wasn't allowed to kick,
and you were really mad at him?

00:45:55.423 --> 00:45:57.425
No,Joseph.

00:46:38.758 --> 00:46:41.469
How much did you take off?

00:46:43.346 --> 00:46:45.890
I lied.

00:46:48.434 --> 00:46:50.436
You added?

00:46:58.319 --> 00:47:00.321
How much is it?

00:47:01.781 --> 00:47:03.783
270 pounds.

00:47:07.328 --> 00:47:09.330
Let's put more.

00:47:12.584 --> 00:47:14.043
Okay.

00:47:18.214 --> 00:47:20.967
Why don't you move back a little
just to be safe, okay?

00:47:53.833 --> 00:47:55.752
More?

00:48:07.013 --> 00:48:10.850
You should never do anything like this.
You know that, right?

00:48:12.644 --> 00:48:15.146
What do you do
if something bad happens?

00:48:15.230 --> 00:48:17.732
Get Mom.

00:48:17.816 --> 00:48:19.692
Right.

00:48:54.894 --> 00:48:57.689
How much did you put on that time?

00:49:01.609 --> 00:49:03.486
All of it.

00:49:05.238 --> 00:49:07.240
What else can we use?

00:49:33.850 --> 00:49:35.852
How much is it?

00:49:44.777 --> 00:49:46.779
How much is it, Dad?

00:49:49.741 --> 00:49:52.285
About 350 pounds.

00:49:59.501 --> 00:50:01.461
Fracture of the fifth metacarpal
of the right hand...

00:50:01.544 --> 00:50:04.923
as well as multiple fractures of
the sixth, seventh and eighth ribs.

00:50:05.006 --> 00:50:07.550
The worst of the injury, however,
was sustained to the right leg...

00:50:07.634 --> 00:50:09.636
in the form of a spiral fracture.

00:50:09.719 --> 00:50:11.721
There were 14 breaks.

00:50:11.804 --> 00:50:14.682
It simply shattered.

00:50:14.766 --> 00:50:17.352
They call me Mr Glass.

00:50:17.435 --> 00:50:21.147
- Who does?
- Kids.

00:50:21.231 --> 00:50:23.316
Are you all right, Mr Price?

00:50:23.399 --> 00:50:25.401
Shall I continue?

00:50:26.736 --> 00:50:29.113
Pins were placed throughout
the length of the leg.

00:50:29.197 --> 00:50:31.950
The use of a wheelchair will be needed
for a two-month period.

00:50:32.033 --> 00:50:35.453
The use of crutches will follow
for 12 to 14 months.

00:50:35.537 --> 00:50:37.705
Hospital stay will range
from five to eight days...

00:50:37.789 --> 00:50:40.625
followed by nine to twelve months
of physical therapy.

00:50:40.708 --> 00:50:43.419
Prescribed medication for pain
management will take the usual forms...

00:50:43.503 --> 00:50:46.297
of morphine drip, percocet, darvocet.

00:50:57.809 --> 00:50:59.894
Your, uh, 10:00 is here.

00:50:59.978 --> 00:51:02.105
The hospital discharged him
this morning.

00:51:04.315 --> 00:51:06.317
Thanks.

00:51:14.742 --> 00:51:16.202
Elijah, right?

00:51:16.286 --> 00:51:20.123
We're gonna prevent any substantial
atrophy of your good leg with this...

00:51:20.206 --> 00:51:22.458
and it works your quadriceps.

00:51:23.585 --> 00:51:25.795
How long have you been married?

00:51:28.506 --> 00:51:31.467
- Twelve years.
- How'd you get together?

00:51:33.720 --> 00:51:35.722
I'm a little nervous being here.

00:51:35.805 --> 00:51:39.267
I ask too many questions
when I'm nervous.

00:51:41.352 --> 00:51:43.354
A car accident.

00:51:43.438 --> 00:51:47.192
Oh. And now you're gonna
have to tell me more.

00:51:51.571 --> 00:51:54.073
My husband was a star athlete
in college...

00:51:54.157 --> 00:51:56.201
and we were in
an accident together.

00:51:57.827 --> 00:52:01.873
Our car flipped on an icy road and we were both
injured, and he couldn't play football any more.

00:52:01.956 --> 00:52:04.751
And if that hadn't happened,
we probably wouldn't have been together.

00:52:04.834 --> 00:52:08.546
- How so?
- I think we should talk about your rehab.

00:52:08.630 --> 00:52:10.965
You don't have to answer
if you don't want to.

00:52:12.091 --> 00:52:15.595
So, tell me more
about the quad machine.

00:52:16.930 --> 00:52:19.849
It prevents atrophy by-

00:52:21.601 --> 00:52:23.812
I couldn't spend my life
with someone who played football.

00:52:23.895 --> 00:52:25.897
It's pretty much that simple.

00:52:27.065 --> 00:52:30.276
I mean, I don't hate the game. I admire
the amount of skill it involves.

00:52:30.360 --> 00:52:33.154
And-And like everyone else,
I was in awe of the way he played it.

00:52:33.238 --> 00:52:37.492
But football, in many ways,
is the opposite of what I do.

00:52:38.743 --> 00:52:41.246
You're rewarded the more
you punish your opponent.

00:52:41.329 --> 00:52:44.791
You know, it's too much about violence,
and I don't want violence in my life.

00:52:46.084 --> 00:52:49.754
It's not a thing many people
can understand, but-

00:52:49.838 --> 00:52:52.924
Anyway, fate stepped in
with that car accident...

00:52:53.007 --> 00:52:55.260
and took football out of the equation.

00:52:55.343 --> 00:52:58.263
And everyone lived happily ever after.

00:53:00.306 --> 00:53:01.933
Sort of.

00:53:02.016 --> 00:53:04.686
What part of David's body was injured?

00:53:06.563 --> 00:53:09.399
Who said my husband's name was David?

00:53:17.157 --> 00:53:19.159
Ladies and gentlemen-

00:53:30.879 --> 00:53:32.881
In the first half-

00:54:02.035 --> 00:54:04.579
A 737 crashes on takeoff-

00:54:04.662 --> 00:54:07.624
172 die, no survivors.

00:54:07.707 --> 00:54:12.086
A hotel fire downtown-
211 die, no survivors.

00:54:12.170 --> 00:54:16.132
An Eastrail train derails
71/2 miles outside the city-

00:54:16.216 --> 00:54:18.218
131 die...

00:54:18.301 --> 00:54:20.386
one survivor.

00:54:20.470 --> 00:54:22.764
He is unharmed.

00:54:22.847 --> 00:54:25.767
I've spoken with your husband
about his survival.

00:54:25.850 --> 00:54:28.686
I suggested a rather
unbelievable possibility.

00:54:28.770 --> 00:54:31.940
Since then, I've come to believe
that possibility...

00:54:32.023 --> 00:54:34.025
however unbelievable...

00:54:34.108 --> 00:54:36.569
is now more a probability.

00:54:36.653 --> 00:54:39.531
And what was it you suggested?

00:54:39.614 --> 00:54:42.325
These are mediocre times, Mrs Dunn.

00:54:42.408 --> 00:54:45.995
People are starting to lose hope.
It's hard for many to believe...

00:54:46.079 --> 00:54:50.124
there are extraordinary things
inside themselves as well as others.

00:54:50.208 --> 00:54:53.336
I hope you can keep an open mind.

00:55:35.336 --> 00:55:37.922
Excuse me, sir?

00:55:38.006 --> 00:55:40.425
Can you step out of line, please?

00:55:44.554 --> 00:55:48.516
We've been having some problems with
people selling drugs here in the stadium.

00:55:48.600 --> 00:55:51.060
Would you mind if I check your pockets?

00:55:52.187 --> 00:55:54.898
Raise your arms, please.

00:55:54.981 --> 00:55:56.983
Come on, raise them up.

00:55:57.066 --> 00:55:59.277
I just got here, man.

00:56:09.871 --> 00:56:11.915
Can I put my hands down now?

00:56:17.670 --> 00:56:19.672
Can I go?

00:56:20.798 --> 00:56:22.800
Yeah.

00:56:24.344 --> 00:56:26.346
Hope you find them.

00:56:35.605 --> 00:56:39.901
- YO, Dunn.
- Yeah.

00:56:39.984 --> 00:56:43.029
I just came into the office.
Your kid was hurt.

00:56:44.280 --> 00:56:47.492
- Where is he?
- Some play rehearsal at school.

00:56:47.575 --> 00:56:49.828
He wants you to come down there.

00:57:04.300 --> 00:57:06.803
Is that your dad?

00:57:10.014 --> 00:57:13.184
I bet my dad could beat up your dad.

00:57:16.646 --> 00:57:19.816
No, he, uh, he insisted
we call only you...

00:57:19.899 --> 00:57:21.985
though we had some trouble
tracking you down.

00:57:22.068 --> 00:57:24.112
I mean, you're not on our list.

00:57:25.405 --> 00:57:26.990
Audrey handles this type of stuff.

00:57:27.073 --> 00:57:29.784
Oh. What type of stuff?

00:57:31.244 --> 00:57:33.246
Joseph stuff.

00:57:36.332 --> 00:57:38.751
Do I need to put any smelly ointment
on him or anything?

00:57:38.835 --> 00:57:40.837
No, no, it's more emotional damage.

00:57:40.920 --> 00:57:44.465
Not, uh- Not to serious, physically.

00:57:44.549 --> 00:57:48.052
Nothing like when I sent you
to the hospital.

00:57:52.015 --> 00:57:54.225
When was that?

00:57:54.309 --> 00:57:58.938
My office was on the other side
of the building back then.

00:58:01.399 --> 00:58:04.068
You don't remember me, do you?

00:58:06.112 --> 00:58:10.158
- No, ma'am.
- I had red hair.

00:58:12.410 --> 00:58:17.165
Well, you were a little younger
than Joseph when it happened.

00:58:17.248 --> 00:58:20.835
Did you know that we
changed the rules of conduct...

00:58:20.919 --> 00:58:23.713
around the pool because of you?

00:58:26.132 --> 00:58:28.134
The kids still tell about it...

00:58:28.218 --> 00:58:31.679
like it was some sort of ghost story.

00:58:31.763 --> 00:58:36.059
"Did you know there was a kid
nearly drowned in that pool?

00:58:37.352 --> 00:58:40.730
He lay on the bottom of the pool
for five minutes.

00:58:40.814 --> 00:58:45.026
And when they pulled him out,
he was dead. "

00:58:49.656 --> 00:58:53.701
We let them tell it.
It helps keep them safe.

00:58:57.288 --> 00:58:59.833
You still phobic of water?

00:59:02.836 --> 00:59:04.879
It was Potter and another guy.

00:59:06.214 --> 00:59:10.176
They were messing with
this Chinese girl in the dressing room.

00:59:10.260 --> 00:59:13.596
Y- You can't let bad things
happen to good people, right?

00:59:14.722 --> 00:59:18.226
That's your code, right?
That's the hero's code.

00:59:19.727 --> 00:59:21.729
I tried to make them stop...

00:59:21.813 --> 00:59:25.900
but they kept pushing me down,
and they wouldn't let me get back up.

00:59:28.695 --> 00:59:31.531
I thought maybe 'cause you're my dad...

00:59:32.657 --> 00:59:34.993
I thought I might be like you.

00:59:38.580 --> 00:59:40.582
I'm not like you.

00:59:42.458 --> 00:59:45.670
You are like me.

00:59:45.753 --> 00:59:47.964
We can both get hurt.

00:59:49.299 --> 00:59:53.511
- I'm just an ordinary man.
- No, you're not.

00:59:53.595 --> 00:59:56.431
Why do you keep saying that?

01:00:04.147 --> 01:00:07.442
Elijah Price came to visit me
at the centre today.

01:00:08.568 --> 01:00:11.446
Jesus.

01:00:11.529 --> 01:00:14.282
He didn't do anything. He just...

01:00:14.365 --> 01:00:16.367
told me his theory.

01:00:17.494 --> 01:00:20.163
That's sad when patients get like that.

01:00:20.246 --> 01:00:22.248
They lose reality.

01:00:27.212 --> 01:00:29.756
Joseph, what the hell are you doing?

01:00:29.839 --> 01:00:31.841
Oh, my God.

01:00:31.925 --> 01:00:35.720
You don't believe. I'll show you.
You can't get hurt.

01:00:35.803 --> 01:00:38.723
That gun's not loaded. He doesn't
know where I keep the bullets.

01:00:38.806 --> 01:00:41.851
In your Rookie of the Year trophy.

01:00:41.935 --> 01:00:44.729
Joseph, did you load the gun?

01:00:44.813 --> 01:00:48.483
- You won't get hurt.
- Elijah was wrong.

01:00:48.566 --> 01:00:51.069
- When did he meet Elijah?
- He was with me when I met him.

01:00:51.152 --> 01:00:53.154
No one believes him.

01:00:53.238 --> 01:00:56.199
Joseph, listen to me.

01:00:56.282 --> 01:01:01.412
Sometimes when people get sick or hurt
for a long time, like Elijah...

01:01:01.496 --> 01:01:05.375
their mind gets hurt too, and they
start to think things that aren't true.

01:01:05.458 --> 01:01:09.254
He told me what he thought
about your father. It isn't true.

01:01:09.337 --> 01:01:11.339
I'll show you.

01:01:13.967 --> 01:01:18.012
Do you remember the story about the
- about the boy that almost drowned in the pool?

01:01:18.096 --> 01:01:20.765
That was me they were talking about.
I almost died. That was me.

01:01:20.849 --> 01:01:23.643
- You're lying.
- I'm not lying, okay? I just didn't remember it, that's all.

01:01:23.726 --> 01:01:25.895
Joseph, you know your father
was injured in college.

01:01:25.979 --> 01:01:28.815
You know that.
You know all about that.

01:01:29.941 --> 01:01:32.485
Don't do it.
He'll die,Joseph.

01:01:32.569 --> 01:01:37.073
- I'll just shoot him once.
- Joseph, listen to what your moth-

01:01:37.157 --> 01:01:39.159
Don't be scared.

01:01:40.368 --> 01:01:42.370
Joseph...

01:01:42.453 --> 01:01:44.998
if you pull that trigger,
I'm going to leave.

01:01:45.081 --> 01:01:48.459
Do you understand?
I'm going to go to New York.

01:01:48.543 --> 01:01:52.046
Y- Y-You're right.
If you pull that trigger...

01:01:52.130 --> 01:01:55.383
that bullet is just gonna bounce off me,
and I'm not going to be hurt.

01:01:55.466 --> 01:01:57.802
But then I'm going to go upstairs
and I'm gonna pack...

01:01:57.886 --> 01:02:01.097
and I'm going to leave for New York.

01:02:01.181 --> 01:02:06.102
- Why?
- Because I thought we were just starting to be friends for real.

01:02:06.186 --> 01:02:08.188
And friends'll listen to each other.
They don't-

01:02:08.271 --> 01:02:12.108
And-And they don't shoot each other,
uh, uh, do they, Audrey?

01:02:12.192 --> 01:02:15.236
N- No shooting friends,Joseph.

01:02:15.320 --> 01:02:17.780
Joseph!

01:02:17.864 --> 01:02:20.992
You are about to be in big trouble!

01:02:22.118 --> 01:02:24.120
Now, I am your father,
and I am telling you...

01:02:24.204 --> 01:02:27.415
to put that goddamn gun down
right now!

01:02:27.499 --> 01:02:30.335
One, two-

01:02:49.270 --> 01:02:51.689
I followed the guy
in the camouflage jacket.

01:02:53.608 --> 01:02:59.030
He had a silver gun with a black grip
tucked in the back of his pants.

01:03:00.824 --> 01:03:04.077
Were you really injured
in that car accident in college?

01:03:04.160 --> 01:03:07.664
'Cause I believe you faked it.
I believe you took the opportunity...

01:03:07.747 --> 01:03:10.500
to end your football career,
no questions asked.

01:03:10.583 --> 01:03:14.337
And I think you did it,
of all things, for a woman.

01:03:14.420 --> 01:03:16.422
I guess that makes sense.

01:03:16.506 --> 01:03:19.759
Football's what, just ten years?

01:03:19.843 --> 01:03:24.430
But love?
Hmm. Now, that's forever.

01:03:26.766 --> 01:03:29.978
And that little bit of sadness
in the mornings you spoke of?

01:03:30.061 --> 01:03:32.313
I think I know what that is.

01:03:32.397 --> 01:03:35.900
Perhaps you're not doing
what you're supposed to be doing.

01:03:35.984 --> 01:03:37.986
Most guns have a black
or silver handle.

01:03:38.069 --> 01:03:40.071
I had a 50-50 shot
of getting the colour right.

01:03:40.155 --> 01:03:43.283
- That's not what I witnessed.
- Stop.

01:03:43.366 --> 01:03:46.661
Stop messing with my life, Elijah.

01:03:46.744 --> 01:03:50.331
My son almost shot me last night because
he wanted to prove you were right.

01:03:50.415 --> 01:03:52.417
I never said you couldn't be killed.

01:03:52.500 --> 01:03:54.502
- I never said that.
- My wife was right.

01:03:54.586 --> 01:03:59.424
There have been three major disasters,
and you were the only one unharmed.

01:03:59.507 --> 01:04:01.509
I have been sick.

01:04:03.720 --> 01:04:08.433
When I was a kid, I spent a week in the
hospital getting better from pneumonia.

01:04:08.516 --> 01:04:12.270
I almost drowned.
Two skinny little kids...

01:04:12.353 --> 01:04:15.857
were fooling around in a pool dunking me
and I swallowed some water.

01:04:15.940 --> 01:04:19.068
They didn't know it,
and it almost killed me.

01:04:19.152 --> 01:04:21.738
Heroes don't get killed like that.

01:04:21.821 --> 01:04:24.073
Normal people do, right?

01:04:25.658 --> 01:04:28.578
I don't need to see you any more, okay?

01:04:30.163 --> 01:04:32.665
Please stay away from my family.

01:04:41.341 --> 01:04:44.469
She said I could tell stories
that could make you cry

01:04:44.552 --> 01:04:46.596
What about you

01:04:46.679 --> 01:04:48.890
Hey, man, it's 20 after.
It's time to choose.

01:04:48.973 --> 01:04:50.975
I gotta head.

01:04:51.059 --> 01:04:55.271
And she sighed, ahh
I said, I want to be a singer

01:04:55.355 --> 01:04:58.775
You better not be jacking off to the
Japanese comics, I swear to God.

01:05:00.652 --> 01:05:03.780
Let's go, let's sit
Let's talk politics

01:05:03.863 --> 01:05:06.783
Goes so good with beer
And while we're at it, baby

01:05:06.866 --> 01:05:09.369
Why don't you tell me
one of your biggest fears

01:05:09.452 --> 01:05:12.580
I said, losing my penis
to a whore with disease

01:05:12.664 --> 01:05:14.791
Uh, look, man, I didn't
know you were in a-

01:05:14.874 --> 01:05:17.085
Losin'my life to
a whore with disease

01:05:17.168 --> 01:05:20.129
- Just choose something, all right?
- Excuse me, please

01:05:25.051 --> 01:05:27.053
The baby-sitter's here.

01:05:29.973 --> 01:05:33.143
- Should we cancel?
- I'm fine.

01:05:36.146 --> 01:05:38.940
We can do this another time.

01:05:39.023 --> 01:05:41.025
Don't lie.

01:05:43.069 --> 01:05:45.738
I'm fine. I just got mixed up.

01:05:53.079 --> 01:05:55.748
How about we just go
for a couple drinks?

01:06:01.421 --> 01:06:04.174
Okay, look, man,
I'm-I'm just gonna wheel you out.

01:06:04.257 --> 01:06:06.259
All right? You can think about things
outside on the sidewalk.

01:06:06.342 --> 01:06:08.344
I gotta get some chicken in me,
you know what I'm sayin'?

01:06:08.428 --> 01:06:11.598
I've been tired, I've been tired

01:06:11.681 --> 01:06:16.603
I've been tired, I've been tired
I've been tired

01:06:25.445 --> 01:06:28.740
- I told the tale of a girl
- Shit!

01:06:28.823 --> 01:06:31.075
She's a little bit older than me

01:06:31.159 --> 01:06:33.912
Strong legs, strong face
voice like milk

01:06:33.995 --> 01:06:35.997
Breasts like a cluster of grapes

01:06:36.080 --> 01:06:38.374
I can't escape her ways

01:06:38.458 --> 01:06:40.460
She raise me

01:06:44.756 --> 01:06:48.760
- Dude.
- Even if you have no one

01:06:48.843 --> 01:06:50.887
Man, I don't care if you are in
a wheelchair. If you do that again...

01:06:50.970 --> 01:06:53.515
I'm calling 5-0.

01:06:53.598 --> 01:06:55.683
And while you're at it, baby

01:06:55.767 --> 01:06:57.769
Man.

01:07:03.316 --> 01:07:07.946
You don't want to sleep
after setting my loins on fire

01:07:08.029 --> 01:07:11.407
That's it, crackerjack. You're gonna
be sitting your ass in jail now.

01:07:11.491 --> 01:07:16.204
I've been tired, I've been tired
I've been tired

01:07:16.287 --> 01:07:19.833
I've been tired, I've been tired

01:07:29.551 --> 01:07:32.720
I've been tired, I've been tired

01:07:32.804 --> 01:07:35.974
- I've been tired, I've been tired
- How much for this one?

01:07:36.057 --> 01:07:37.559
I've been tired

01:07:39.018 --> 01:07:42.397
- Rust?
- Yeah.

01:07:42.480 --> 01:07:44.816
As a colour, not as rust.

01:07:44.899 --> 01:07:48.820
You know, like rust-coloured
paint or wood.

01:07:50.613 --> 01:07:53.908
- I didn't know that.
- Mm-hmm.

01:07:53.992 --> 01:07:56.578
Mine's still brown.

01:07:56.661 --> 01:07:58.663
Okay, my turn.

01:07:58.746 --> 01:08:00.957
Favourite song?

01:08:01.040 --> 01:08:05.211
"Soft and Wet" by the Artist
Formerly Known as Prince.

01:08:05.295 --> 01:08:07.630
What?

01:08:07.714 --> 01:08:10.466
We're supposed to be honest.

01:08:10.550 --> 01:08:12.969
"Soft And Wet. "

01:08:13.052 --> 01:08:15.388
That's very interesting.

01:08:15.472 --> 01:08:17.474
Okay, my turn.

01:08:19.184 --> 01:08:21.394
When was the first time...

01:08:22.729 --> 01:08:25.773
the thought popped into your head
we might not make it?

01:08:27.275 --> 01:08:29.277
That's not the game.

01:08:29.360 --> 01:08:32.405
It's the first date.
There aren't any rules.

01:08:36.576 --> 01:08:40.121
- Don't know for sure.
- Think carefully.

01:08:41.414 --> 01:08:43.416
What about the game?

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:45.502
It's over. I won.

01:08:47.504 --> 01:08:49.506
Look, maybe it wasn't
a specific moment.

01:08:49.589 --> 01:08:54.344
- Maybe it was a time-
- I had a nightmare one night...

01:08:54.427 --> 01:09:00.266
and I didn't wake you up so you
could tell me that it was okay.

01:09:01.768 --> 01:09:04.145
I think that was the first time.

01:09:06.189 --> 01:09:08.191
Does that count?

01:09:09.734 --> 01:09:11.736
That counts.

01:09:15.448 --> 01:09:19.327
Do you knowingly keep me
and Joseph at a distance?

01:09:27.043 --> 01:09:29.462
Yes.

01:09:29.546 --> 01:09:31.548
Why?

01:09:33.716 --> 01:09:35.718
I don't know.

01:09:40.223 --> 01:09:42.809
I just don't feel right, Audrey.

01:09:44.227 --> 01:09:46.604
Something's...

01:09:46.688 --> 01:09:48.898
just not right.

01:09:51.025 --> 01:09:54.195
Do you resent us, David?

01:09:54.279 --> 01:09:56.781
Resent the life you have?

01:09:58.700 --> 01:10:02.328
I mean, there were a lot of other things
you could've done after college.

01:10:02.412 --> 01:10:04.789
These were your choices.

01:10:09.460 --> 01:10:11.754
You know, even if it meant
we couldn't have been together...

01:10:11.838 --> 01:10:15.300
I never would've wished
that injury on you.

01:10:15.383 --> 01:10:17.844
What you could do physically...

01:10:17.927 --> 01:10:20.180
was a gift.

01:10:20.263 --> 01:10:23.057
I never would've wished it to go away.

01:10:25.268 --> 01:10:27.270
You know that, right?

01:10:31.483 --> 01:10:34.319
You had two calls after Joseph
went to bed. One came through...

01:10:34.402 --> 01:10:36.696
while I was on the other line,
but I wasn't talking too long.

01:10:36.779 --> 01:10:40.617
There was an emergency with my sister. She tried to do
her own perm, and now she looks like she stuck her head-

01:10:40.700 --> 01:10:42.827
Who called through?

01:10:42.911 --> 01:10:45.330
Um, someone from New York...

01:10:45.413 --> 01:10:47.457
uh, about a security job.

01:10:47.540 --> 01:10:50.752
They want to hire you. I didn't know
you guys were moving to New York.

01:10:50.835 --> 01:10:53.254
Thanks for telling me.

01:10:53.338 --> 01:10:55.924
We weren't all gonna move.

01:10:57.091 --> 01:10:59.093
Oh.

01:11:01.012 --> 01:11:04.349
I let the answering machine
pick up the other call.

01:11:08.478 --> 01:11:10.480
Great.

01:11:21.991 --> 01:11:25.787
Look, let's just be honest here.
We're just at the beginning...

01:11:25.870 --> 01:11:28.873
and I don't expect
you or I to change...

01:11:28.957 --> 01:11:31.417
the course of where
our lives were headed...

01:11:31.501 --> 01:11:33.795
because of one date.

01:11:33.878 --> 01:11:38.341
And if you do go to New York,
we can develop this.

01:11:38.424 --> 01:11:41.594
We'll just be forced to take it slow.

01:11:41.678 --> 01:11:45.431
And in the end, I think
that's definitely better.

01:11:47.976 --> 01:11:50.270
I mean, this is our second time around,
David. I didn't expect us...

01:11:50.353 --> 01:11:52.647
to get carried away.

01:11:54.899 --> 01:11:58.778
But I guess "congratulations"
is the right thing to say.

01:12:23.553 --> 01:12:25.805
David, it's Elijah.

01:12:25.889 --> 01:12:27.891
It was so obvious.

01:12:27.974 --> 01:12:30.310
It was this one issue
that brought it back for me-

01:12:30.393 --> 01:12:32.395
Century Comics 117.

01:12:32.479 --> 01:12:34.606
That's where this group,
the Coalition of Evil...

01:12:34.689 --> 01:12:37.192
tried to ascertain the weakness
of every superhero...

01:12:37.275 --> 01:12:40.695
because they all have one,
just like you.

01:12:40.778 --> 01:12:44.824
Your bones don't break.
Mine do. That's clear.

01:12:44.908 --> 01:12:48.369
Your cells react to bacteria
and viruses differently than mine.

01:12:48.453 --> 01:12:52.415
You don't get sick.
I do. That's also clear.

01:12:52.499 --> 01:12:57.795
But for some reason, you and I
react the exact same way to water.

01:12:57.879 --> 01:13:00.298
We swallow it too fast, we choke.

01:13:00.381 --> 01:13:02.634
We get some in our lungs, we drown.

01:13:02.717 --> 01:13:07.806
However unreal it may seem,
we are connected, you and I.

01:13:07.889 --> 01:13:12.560
We're on the same curve,
just on opposite ends.

01:13:12.644 --> 01:13:16.689
The point of all this is we
now know something we didn't.

01:13:16.773 --> 01:13:20.318
You have a weakness- water.

01:13:20.401 --> 01:13:23.363
It's like your kryptonite.

01:13:23.446 --> 01:13:25.740
You hearing me, David?

01:15:40.708 --> 01:15:42.710
Audrey?

01:16:16.119 --> 01:16:18.538
Gotcha. Come on.

01:16:36.139 --> 01:16:38.975
Audrey. Audrey.

01:16:44.856 --> 01:16:46.858
Hey!

01:16:50.945 --> 01:16:53.823
You'll be okay.

01:16:53.907 --> 01:16:57.702
What- What happened?

01:16:57.785 --> 01:17:01.706
I thought I was-
I thought I was dead.

01:17:01.789 --> 01:17:03.791
Me too.

01:17:08.254 --> 01:17:10.256
Is she all right?

01:17:10.340 --> 01:17:12.675
I think her leg's broken.

01:17:12.759 --> 01:17:15.303
Are you hurt?

01:17:15.386 --> 01:17:17.597
Hey, man, are you hurt?

01:17:48.044 --> 01:17:50.046
Hello.

01:17:50.129 --> 01:17:52.882
I wasn't injured in that car accident.

01:17:52.966 --> 01:17:55.593
David.

01:17:55.677 --> 01:17:58.221
I've never been injured, Elijah.

01:18:00.557 --> 01:18:02.851
What am I supposed to do?

01:18:08.815 --> 01:18:11.693
Go to where people are.

01:18:11.776 --> 01:18:14.779
You won't have to look very long.

01:18:16.406 --> 01:18:19.367
It's all right to be afraid, David...

01:18:19.450 --> 01:18:23.496
because this part won't be
like a comic book.

01:18:23.580 --> 01:18:28.459
Real life doesn't fit into little boxes
that were drawn for it.

01:19:06.789 --> 01:19:10.752
There's one in the first row.
It's- It's the second one.

01:19:10.835 --> 01:19:13.713
Yes. It's the second one over.

01:19:46.871 --> 01:19:49.040
Go back to Africa!

01:20:05.348 --> 01:20:07.600
Hey, what's your name?

01:20:13.231 --> 01:20:15.441
I think you drank too much.

01:21:01.070 --> 01:21:03.114
Can I come in?

01:21:03.198 --> 01:21:05.742
Who are you?

01:21:05.825 --> 01:21:08.620
I like your house.

01:21:08.703 --> 01:21:10.705
Can I come in?

01:21:10.788 --> 01:21:12.999
What is this?

01:21:14.667 --> 01:21:17.962
No, you can't come in.

01:21:18.046 --> 01:21:20.507
Are you sure?

01:21:20.590 --> 01:21:22.884
What are- What are you-

01:25:53.071 --> 01:25:55.073
It's okay.

01:26:05.416 --> 01:26:07.418
It's okay. It's okay.

01:32:51.114 --> 01:32:53.700
I had a bad dream.

01:32:59.581 --> 01:33:01.749
It's over now.

01:33:29.736 --> 01:33:32.572
I don't know.

01:33:32.655 --> 01:33:34.741
I can't believe you'd think that.

01:33:34.824 --> 01:33:36.826
I'm just asking you.

01:33:40.079 --> 01:33:42.290
I'm making French toast.

01:33:57.722 --> 01:34:00.308
I've been thinking about Elijah Price.

01:34:01.601 --> 01:34:05.396
If he shows up again, I think
we should call the police, okay?

01:34:09.484 --> 01:34:11.486
Okay?

01:34:13.988 --> 01:34:15.990
Okay.

01:35:24.100 --> 01:35:26.186
You were right.

01:36:15.777 --> 01:36:19.864
This is one of Johann Davis'
earliest drawings.

01:36:19.948 --> 01:36:22.325
See the villain's eyes?

01:36:22.408 --> 01:36:24.661
They're larger than
the other characters'.

01:36:24.744 --> 01:36:30.250
They insinuate a slightly skewed
perspective on how they see the world-

01:36:31.376 --> 01:36:33.670
just off normal.

01:36:33.753 --> 01:36:36.089
He doesn't look scary.

01:36:36.172 --> 01:36:38.675
Mm-hmm. That's what I said to my son.

01:36:38.758 --> 01:36:41.427
But he says there's always two kinds.

01:36:41.511 --> 01:36:45.932
There's the soldier villain
who fights the hero with his hands...

01:36:46.015 --> 01:36:50.311
and then there's the real threat-
the brilliant and evil archenemy...

01:36:50.395 --> 01:36:52.897
who fights the hero with his mind.

01:36:52.981 --> 01:36:54.983
Are you Elijah's mother?

01:36:55.066 --> 01:36:58.820
I am. I'm helping him with the sale.

01:36:58.903 --> 01:37:01.698
Nice to meet you. I'm David Dunn.

01:37:01.781 --> 01:37:03.783
He's spoken of you.

01:37:03.867 --> 01:37:05.869
Says you're becoming friends.

01:37:05.952 --> 01:37:08.371
We are.

01:37:08.454 --> 01:37:10.665
Looks like he's doing good today.

01:37:11.791 --> 01:37:14.711
I'm very proud of him.

01:37:14.794 --> 01:37:17.881
He's come through a lot in his life-

01:37:17.964 --> 01:37:21.509
a couple of bad spills
I thought had broken him.

01:37:21.593 --> 01:37:24.721
Mm-hmm. They were bad...

01:37:25.847 --> 01:37:28.391
but he made it.

01:37:28.475 --> 01:37:30.477
Yes, he did.

01:37:31.603 --> 01:37:33.813
He's kind of a miracle.

01:37:35.982 --> 01:37:37.984
Yes, he is.

01:37:41.529 --> 01:37:44.199
- I'll tell him you're here.
- Thank you.

01:37:45.533 --> 01:37:49.287
We'll work something out.
Always able to work something out.

01:38:14.354 --> 01:38:16.356
It has begun.

01:38:19.484 --> 01:38:21.611
Tell me something, David.

01:38:22.737 --> 01:38:27.283
When you woke up this morning,
was it still there?

01:38:27.367 --> 01:38:30.245
The sadness?

01:38:30.328 --> 01:38:32.330
No.

01:38:35.917 --> 01:38:38.962
I think this is where we shake hands.

01:38:57.981 --> 01:39:01.025
- Look!
- Did you see it?

01:39:10.410 --> 01:39:12.912
I worked in that building 25 years.

01:39:12.996 --> 01:39:15.123
I know all its secrets.

01:39:16.583 --> 01:39:18.585
Secrets?

01:39:20.003 --> 01:39:24.924
Like if there ever was a fire
on floors one, two or three...

01:39:25.008 --> 01:39:28.511
everyone in that hotel
would be burned alive.

01:39:34.476 --> 01:39:37.228
Passengers aren't allowed in there.

01:40:20.522 --> 01:40:22.982
Do you know what
the scariest thing is?

01:40:26.694 --> 01:40:29.989
To not know your place
in this world...

01:40:30.073 --> 01:40:32.617
to not know why you're here.

01:40:33.910 --> 01:40:35.912
That's-

01:40:37.747 --> 01:40:40.166
That's just an awful feeling.

01:40:41.543 --> 01:40:43.878
What have you done?

01:40:45.046 --> 01:40:48.091
I almost gave up hope.

01:40:48.174 --> 01:40:51.386
There were so many times
I questioned myself.

01:40:51.469 --> 01:40:54.013
You killed all those people.

01:40:55.306 --> 01:40:58.143
But I found you.

01:40:58.226 --> 01:41:01.521
So many sacrifices...

01:41:02.647 --> 01:41:04.649
just to find you.

01:41:04.732 --> 01:41:06.734
Jesus Christ!

01:41:16.619 --> 01:41:19.414
Now that we know who you are...

01:41:20.540 --> 01:41:23.251
I know who I am.

01:41:26.838 --> 01:41:29.048
I'm not a mistake.

01:41:30.550 --> 01:41:32.719
It all makes sense.

01:41:32.802 --> 01:41:37.390
In a comic, you know how you can tell
who the arch-villain's going to be?

01:41:37.474 --> 01:41:40.852
He's the exact opposite of the hero.

01:41:40.935 --> 01:41:44.689
And most times, they're friends,
like you and me.

01:41:44.772 --> 01:41:48.610
I should've known way back when.
You know why, David?

01:41:48.693 --> 01:41:50.695
Because of the kids.

01:42:00.622 --> 01:42:03.291
They called me Mr Glass.

